<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO CHET &amp; CHRIS</font><br>
<tt>Mon Mar 17 20:36:20 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Chet, Boy did some of that hit home. Samo, Samo, here on<br>
the way we got to return. One day Killin Charles, the next<br>
eating burgers at Dairy Queen. Also the sleep pattern. I<br>
can't remember how long it took me to get a full nights<br>
sleep again. What's funny was I remember I didn't want to<br>
change the pattern. There was a basic security involved. I<br>
guess I thought if everybody would just takes  their turn<br>
monitoring the perimeter, The World would be a safer place.<br>
Wierd.<br><br>
Chris, The fact is that there never was any training or<br>
indoctrination that really prepared one for battle. They<br>
prepared you to obey. A few things drove you in battle with<br>
other humans. First fear. Later fear and anger. I've<br>
addressed a few high school classes who wanted a Vet to<br>
ask directly. The combat thing was always what raised the<br>
most curiosity. You get some real pointed questions.<br><br>
It was the fear I remember most. The horror wore off after<br>
a while. I was always most afraid right after killing an<br>
enemy. The sight of a dead man before you, wasted by your<br>
own hand was petrifying. When you looked into those blank<br>
eyes, you saw your own. It bordered on panic. At that<br>
moment, I always felt every weapon in Nam was trained on<br>
me. Maybe the other guys can relate their own gut feelings.<br><br>
I just know a lot of my dreams contain those eyes, and that<br>
skin crawling feeling of you being next.<br><br>
By the way, they only became gooks to me when the anger<br>
kicked in. The anger came from the frustration of how we<br>
fought. Also from the loss of buddies and the betrayal of<br>
&quot;friendly&quot; forces or villages. At some point, to stay sane,<br>
I had to dehumanize them in some way in order to cope with<br>
it. I'm not proud of that, but it would let me try to make<br>
it just one more day. Just one more day. It came down to<br>
that. <br><br>
See Ya, Bro's.<br>

<p><code>-- carnival@ont.com  (JJ the Boonirat) </code><p>


